10:44.880 --> 10:47.075
She ain't coming back.

10:47.480 --> 10:50.278
Three hours she was gone.

10:51.640 --> 10:56.077
And when she finally came back,
she was reeking of Old Spice and pot.

10:56.240 --> 10:59.550
-l see.
-And she didn't even have any ice cream.

11:00.480 --> 11:02.789
All right, let's stop here for a minute. . .

11:02.960 --> 11:06.475
. . .and talk in general
about your feelings towards women.

11:06.640 --> 11:08.631
No, thanks.

11:08.800 --> 11:10.711
-Rather discuss your childhood?
-Nope.

11:10.880 --> 11:13.713
-Father? Mother?
-Dead. Killed him.

11:14.560 --> 11:17.074
-Would you like to discuss that?
-We just did.

11:17.760 --> 11:20.399
Charlie, l'm not sure
we're on the same page here.

11:20.560 --> 11:22.312
Have you ever been in therapy before?

11:22.880 --> 11:26.714
-Does massage therapy count?
-No.

11:26.880 --> 11:29.838
lt's almost the same thing.
One-on-one with a strange woman. . .

11:30.000 --> 11:33.276
. . .who charges you for the hour
and then only gives you 50 minutes?

11:34.920 --> 11:36.797
Why don't we just go back
to your story?

11:36.960 --> 11:39.315
Touch a nerve there, did l?

11:42.040 --> 11:43.234
Okay, okay.

11:43.400 --> 11:47.393
Well, Jake ignored his father
the entire time we were there, so. . .

11:47.800 --> 11:50.314
...Alan was a little upset
when we got back in the car.

11:50.480 --> 11:53.631
He hates me. My only son hates me.

11:53.840 --> 11:57.276
He doesn't hate you. He just
didn't appreciate you telling his friends. . .

11:57.440 --> 12:00.432
. . .that laser tag
can induce epileptic fits.

12:00.600 --> 12:02.591
-Well, it can.
-Be that as it may. . .

12:02.760 --> 12:06.116
. . .you could've gotten your point across
without flopping on the floor. . .

12:06.280 --> 12:09.158
. . .rolling your eyes up,
and pretending to swallow your tongue.

12:09.320 --> 12:13.029
Hey, hey.
A picture is worth a thous--

12:14.760 --> 12:15.795
Charlie, stop the car.

12:16.240 --> 12:17.355
-Why?
-l have to get out.

12:17.520 --> 12:20.034
-l'm feeling claustrophobic.
-There's no place to stop.

12:20.200 --> 12:23.033
-We have to stop!
-Where?

12:23.200 --> 12:25.589
l can't breathe. l can't breathe.
l have to get out.

12:25.760 --> 12:29.309
-l have to get out now. Now, now, now.
-Okay, okay, hold on. Hold on.

12:32.320 --> 12:33.719
The seat belt won't come off.

12:33.880 --> 12:35.757
-Just push the button.
-l can't, l can't.

12:35.920 --> 12:39.469
-lt won't come off. Help me.
-Okay, okay, move your hands.

12:43.160 --> 12:44.639
Okay.

12:45.160 --> 12:48.709
lt's passing. lt's-- Yes. l'm okay.

12:48.880 --> 12:50.359
-No, you're not.
-What?

12:50.800 --> 12:51.869
-Get out.
-What?

12:52.040 --> 12:55.476
Get out now. Now, now, now.
Get out. Get out.

13:02.320 --> 13:04.356
That's better.

13:10.760 --> 13:13.877
So you just left your brother
on the side of the road?

13:14.640 --> 13:16.915
He couldn't believe it either.

13:18.000 --> 13:21.436
You should've seen his face
in the rear-view mirror.

13:21.600 --> 13:25.275
All right, Charlie, we've been talking
for quite a while, and l gotta tell you:

13:25.440 --> 13:28.034
l still don't understand
why you came to see me.

13:28.200 --> 13:29.349
You in a hurry?

13:30.800 --> 13:34.429
Doesn't that undermine your whole
pay-by-the-hour business model?

13:35.720 --> 13:38.439
-Go ahead.
-Thank you.

13:38.600 --> 13:42.309
So as l was driving away,
l decided l needed a little quiet time. . .

13:42.480 --> 13:45.040
. . .for, you know,
reflection and meditation.

13:54.360 --> 13:57.511
-Hey.
-Hey. What took you so long?

13:58.320 --> 14:00.550
l was sure you'd come back.

14:01.880 --> 14:04.474
l guess that's case closed
on the telepathy stuff.

14:06.560 --> 14:10.599
-What are you drinking?
-l don't know, something soothing.

14:11.320 --> 14:13.709
-Kahlua and cream.
-He's kidding. Give him a beer.

14:13.880 --> 14:17.236
-Must you always embarrass me?
-Hey, l have had a traumatic night.

14:17.400 --> 14:19.868
l feel very exposed, vulnerable,
confused--

14:20.040 --> 14:22.315
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Okay, shut up, shut up, shut up.

14:24.240 --> 14:25.559
-Hi.
-Hi.

14:25.720 --> 14:28.757
-Yeah, hi.
-Can we buy you ladies a drink?

14:28.920 --> 14:33.311
-No, thanks. We're already pretty blitzed.
-Boy, are we blitzed.

14:33.480 --> 14:34.549
Perfect.

14:36.000 --> 14:37.319
l'm Charlie. This is Alan.

14:37.480 --> 14:38.993
-Amy.
-Beth.

14:39.160 --> 14:41.469
Nice to meet you.
How's it going tonight?

14:41.640 --> 14:43.710
-Pretty good.
-We're blitzed.

14:45.160 --> 14:48.391
-How about you?
-Yeah, how you doing?

14:48.560 --> 14:51.870
-Oh, boy. Where to start?
-No one's talking to you.

14:52.040 --> 14:54.554
-What's the matter, Alan?
-Yeah, what's the matter?

14:54.720 --> 14:56.438
Well, you really wanna know?

14:56.600 --> 14:59.512
They don't. Trust me, you really don't.

14:59.680 --> 15:02.638
Well, maybe it's a late reaction
to the divorce.

15:02.800 --> 15:07.157
Maybe it's my son not needing me
so much now that he's growing up. . .

15:07.320 --> 15:09.436
. . .but l think it's more than that.

15:09.600 --> 15:12.637
l think it's just life grinding me down,
and l just. . . .

15:13.320 --> 15:15.151
l don't think l can take it anymore.

15:15.640 --> 15:18.791
-Oh, you poor baby.
-Poor, poor baby.

15:18.960 --> 15:21.315
-Tell us all about it.
-Yeah, tell us.

15:21.480 --> 15:24.233
Well, l was never a happy child.

15:24.400 --> 15:26.994
Oh, God, l was a miserable kid.

15:28.520 --> 15:31.353
And the only thing
that gave my life meaning was my son.

15:31.520 --> 15:33.351
At least you've got a son.

15:34.680 --> 15:37.433
l've got nothing, except. . .

15:37.600 --> 15:38.635
. . .epilepsy.

15:40.080 --> 15:41.877
-Oh, no.
-Yeah, oh, no.

15:49.760 --> 15:53.070
So anyway,
there l was on my wedding day. . .

15:53.240 --> 15:55.800
. . .in front of the priest
and all our friends. . .

15:55.960 --> 15:58.633
. . .flopping around on the altar
like an epileptic trout. . .

15:59.600 --> 16:01.352
. . .when l heard her father say:

